<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4441] Fix validation of dates</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4441</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Our date validation (timestamp type) doesn&apos;t validate that the date is correct, i.e. it allows dates like 2011-42-42, because DateUtils.parseDate() doesn&apos;t do the validation (don&apos;t ask me how it can generate a timestamp from bogus date, apparently it can).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easy fix is to use DateUtils.parseDateStrictly(), which does the validation. This does require to update commons-lang to &amp;gt;= 2.5 (we have 2.4).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
